Text.string: Don't run, you'll ruin the taste.
Finally, a worthy opponent! Our battle will be LEGENDARY!
I have killed gods. I fear no badass.
A mighty foe; a worthy challenge.
A titan! Your death will be glorious.
Badass! You'll make a fine feast for the worms.
With every kill, I grow stronger.
Each day, I exceed what I was before.
Power beyond measure, skills beyond counting!
Brother, this will not be your end!
Every second I stand here, I get weaker. Every second my enemies prowl on the hunt, they get stronger. I must move.
This calm reminds me of my years in the solitude and silence of the archives. (beat) I hate it.
While I could stand here and patiently wait for my prey to die of old age over the course of the next century, so far, it is exceedingly boring.
I have heard that certain species of squid hunt by standing still and allowing prey to drift to them. I am not a squid.
Hm. I COULD apply these thirty years of pending system updates. But then I'd have to open all my programs again, which is a total hassle. I'll just set another 24 hour delay. "Remind me tomorrow".
At long last, I feel her near.
Can I die? Have I lived?
I have so much work left to do…
Will they make a trophy of me?
The Hunt will continue… without me…
Rest, now. Your hunt is over.
A meager life. A fitting death.
I thank you for the challenge.
I suggest you learn to fly, quickly.
The fall will come soon enough!
Enjoy the view while it lasts.
I am reborn in the Hunt.
Am I not worthy of Death?
No, that will not be my end.
While there is prey, the hunt continues!
If they thought Death would stop me, they have much to learn.
Oh ho, you want to play?
We'll get back to killing soon. I promise.
I am fond of you as well.
Go, brother, I will call on you.
You may idle elsewhere, for now.
